Malnutrition in Africa - A Study¶

Sub-Saharan Africa has the highest proportion of undernourished children. Malnutrition in children is caused by a variety of factors such as the country's population, gross domestic product, education, and so on.¶

The aim of this study is to analyze the factos that contribute to malnutrition rate of the country
